ActCanada-Chile Free Trade Agreement Implementation Act
SubjectOrder Authorizing to sign, execute and issue and Instrument of Full Powers, subject to ratification, the Exchange of Letters between the Government of Canada and the Government of the Republic of Chile - Amendment
PrecisOrder Authorizing (a) the Minister of Foreign Affairs to sign, on behalf of the Government of Canada, subject to ratification, the EXCHANGE OF LETTERS BETWEEN THE GOVERNMENT OF CANADA AND THE GOVERNMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF CHILE CONSTITUTING AN AGREEMENT TO AMEND THE FREE TRADE AGREEMENT BETWEEN THE GOVERNMENT OF CANADA AND THE REPUBLIC OF CHILE, DONE AT SANTIAGO ON DECEMBER 5, 1996, AS AMENDED; or (b) the Minister of Foreign Affairs to execute and issue an Instrument of Full Powers authorizing the individuals mentioned in the order, to sign, on behalf of the Government of Canada, subject to ratification, the EXCHANGE OF LETTERS BETWEEN THE GOVERNMENT OF CANADA AND THE GOVERNMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF CHILE CONSTITUTING AN AGREEMENT TO AMEND THE FREE TRADE AGREEMENT BETWEEN THE GOVERNMENT OF CANADA AND THE REPUBLIC OF CHILE, DONE AT SANTIAGO ON DECEMBER 5, 1996, AS AMENDED.
